02/11/2007
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Svetozar Marovic, the only president of the previous Serbia-Montenegro entity, denied on Thursday (November 1st) that he plans to run in Montenegro's presidential elections next year. Marovic, a member of the ruling Democratic Party of Socialists (DPS), added that as far as he knows, DPS leader Milo Djukanovic has no plans to pursue the presidency either. Marovic rejected recent speculation he will be taking over DPS's chairmanship from Djukanovic. (Vijesti - 02/11/07; Antena M - 01/11/07)
